    ],
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Sprite button behaviors"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Sprite media is deprecated in the QuickTime file format. The information that follows documents existing content containing sprite media and should not be used for new development.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In QuickTime 4 and later, sprites in a sprite track can specify simple button behaviors. These behaviors can control the sprite’s image, the system cursor, and the status message displayed in a Web browser. They also provide a shortcut for a common set of actions that may result in more efficient QuickTime movies.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Button behaviors can be added to a sprite. These behaviors are intended to make the common task of creating buttons in a sprite track easy — you basically just fill in a template.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Three types of behaviors are available; you may choose one or more behaviors. Each change a type of property associated with a button and are triggered by the mouse states ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "notOverNotPressed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "overNotPressed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "overPressed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "notOverPressed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". The three properties changed are:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The sprite’s ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code": "imageIndex",
                      "type": "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " value",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The ID of a cursor to be displayed",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The ID of a status string variable displayed in the URL status area of a Web browser.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Setting a property’s value to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "–1",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " means don’t change it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The cursor is automatically set back to the default system cursor when leaving a sprite.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The sprite track handles letting one sprite act as an active button at a time.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The behaviors are added at the beginning of the sprite’s list of actions, so they may be overridden by actions if desired.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To use the behaviors, you fill in the new atoms as follows, using the description key specified in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.qtff/documentation/QuickTime-File-Format/QT_atom_container_description_key",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ":",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "kSpriteAtomType",
            "    <kSpriteBehaviorsAtomType>, 1",
            " ",
            "        <kSpriteImageBehaviorAtomType>",
            "            [QTSpriteButtonBehaviorStruct]",
            "        <kSpriteCursorBehaviorAtomType>",
            "            [QTSpriteButtonBehaviorStruct]",
            "        <kSpriteStatusStringsBehaviorAtomType>",
            "            [QTSpriteButtonBehaviorStruct]"
          ],
          "syntax": "c",
          "type": "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
